1/2 lb ground beef
1 pkg (14 oz) frozen pepper strips
1 cup shredded Monterey Jack cheese, divided    
1 can (10 oz) mild enchilada sauce, like 
       Old El Paso, divided
8 flour tortillas (8")

     Makes 4 servings
 


Heat oven to 400F. In nonstick skillet over high heat, cook ground beef 5 min., or until browned, stirring often. Remove skillet from heat.  Add frozen pepper strips, 1/2 cup shredded Monterey jack cheese and 1/4 cup enchilada sauce to skillet; stir to combine. Pour 1/2 cup enchilada sauce in pie plate. Dip each tortilla in sauce, covering both sides. Place 1/2 cup meat-pepper mixture down center of each tortilla. Roll up tortillas and place in a greased 13" x 9" casserole or baking dish. Top beef enchiladas with remaining sauce nad shredded Monterey Jack cheese; bake 10 min., or until enchiladas are heated through.

 
      work time : 5 min
      total time : 20 min
 
   
