      Ingredients & Directions
  
1/2 lb boneless pork
  3 tablespoons soysauce
  8 dried lily buds
  4 Dried Chinese mushrooms,
  4 dried tree ears
  6 cups (homemade) chicken broth
  3 tablespopons rice wine vinegar or white vinegar
1/2 teaspoon pepper
  8 ounces of fresh tofu
  1 tablespoon cold water
  1 tablespoon cornstarch
  1 beaten egg
  2 tablespoons thinly sliced green onion.
 
 
partially freeze pork; cut into 1 x 1/4" strips. Sprinkle meat with 1 tblspn of soy sayce. Meanwhile, in three bowls soak lily buds, mushrooms, and tree ears. Cut off & discard stem end of lily buds. Slice each lily bud into 1-inch lengths. Thoroughly rinse tree ears under running water; drain well. Cut off  & discard mushroom & tree ear stems. Cut mushrooms & tree ears into thin strips. In large suace pan bring broth to boiling; stir in pork, remaining soy suace, lily buds, mushrooms, tree ears, rice wine/white vinegar, and pepper. Simmer, covered, 10 minutes. Slice tofu into 1/4-inch wide strips. Add to soup. Simmer, covered, 3 minutes more. Blend cold water into corn starch. Stir into soup. Pour egg slowlyy into hot soup  in a thin stream, beating constantly with fork until egg cooks and shreds  finely. Cook soup until slightly  thickened & bubbly. Remove from heat. Stir in thinly sliced green onion. 
serves 4. 
Usually doubled.

  

     

    


